DESCRIPTION:Link: https://hulms.instructure.com/courses/4981/discussion_topics/61951\n\nDear everyone\,\nHere’s a brief recap of Lecture 3 (the recording can be found in the meeting chat on Teams).\nWe introduced Ethics &amp\; AI as a taxonomy\, including:\n\nthe difference between ethics vs. morals and what Ethical AI means in practice\nkey pillars: fairness (incl. equality vs. equity)\, accountability\, transparency\, privacy\, and bias\nexplainability vs. interpretability\, and why fairness is a socio-technical issue (not just statistics)\nreal-world examples of AI harms/bias and a preview of tools/platforms we’ll use going forward\n\nThe recap quiz will be based on the lecture and notes\, so please prepare by re-watching the lecture recording and reviewing the slides.\nSupplemental material: papers + reference resources\, including Attention Is All You Need\, On the Dangers of Stochastic Parrots\, AIF360\, and additional readings can be found at Readings &amp\; Supplemental Material.\nAssignment 2 has been released and can be found at A2: Ethics of AI MOOC. It is due on Sunday\, 1st Feb at 11:59 PM.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;\nBest\,\nCS 435 Team
SUMMARY:📢 Lecture 3 Recap\, Quiz & Assignment (CS 435-L1)
