DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260209
DESCRIPTION:Link: https://hulms.instructure.com/courses/5040/discussion_topics/62395\n\n\nDear All\,\nThe following rubric will be used for mid-evaluations of your capstone projects:\n\n\n\nCategory\nMax Score\nAbove Average (8-10 for Design\, 16-20 for Demo\, etc.)\nAverage (6-8 for Design\, 12-16 for Demo\, etc.)\nBelow Average (0-6 for Design\, 0-12 for Demo\, etc.)\n\n\nProgress\n10\nThe Group has demonstrated strong progress by achieving most planned milestones for this stage. Work completed so far is coherent\, well-organized\, and clearly aligned with the project objectives. The team can clearly justify what has been implemented and why.\nThe Group has made reasonable progress and completed several milestones. However\, progress is uneven\, and some completed work appears ad hoc or insufficiently justified. There is partial clarity about what has been achieved and what remains.\nThe Group has shown limited progress\, with few meaningful milestones achieved. Work completed so far lacks direction or coherence\, and there is little clarity about current status or rationale behind the work done.\n\n\nWorking Demo\n20\nThe major functionalities have been completed. All components should be integrated and functional. The test plan has been created and executed.\nCore functionalities have been implemented\, but some may still have minor issues or require refinement. Most components are integrated\, but some may not work seamlessly together. A test plan has been created\, but execution is incomplete or reveals issues that remain unresolved.\nOnly partial implementation of core functionalities\, with major features missing or non-functional. Components are not fully integrated\, leading to significant gaps in functionality. A test plan is missing\, incomplete\, or has not been executed\, making it difficult to assess system performance.\n\n\nRemaining Work\n5\nThe team has shown excellent progress so far and has achieved many milestones. They are clear about the work yet to be completed and can comfortably complete it in time.\nThe team has shown good progress and achieved significant milestones. However\, much work remains\, and they need to pace up. Some components are still vague.\nThe team has not shown good progress. Most important milestones remain unachieved\, and there is no clarity about outstanding tasks\, making completion difficult.\n\n\nPresentation Skills\n7\nThe project is properly introduced. The content is well-organized and presented coherently in an interesting manner. Time was properly managed.\nThe project is properly introduced. The content is reasonably organized and presented coherently. Some information was missing or vague.\nThe project is poorly introduced. The content is disorganized with missing or vague key information.\n\n\nQ&amp\;A\n8\nGroup members were well prepared to answer the questions and showed good knowledge on the topics. They did not leave any room for ambiguity.\nGroup members were prepared to answer questions and showed basic knowledge on the topics. Some ambiguity remained.\nGroup members were not well-prepared to answer questions\, showed limited knowledge\, and left much room for ambiguity.\n\n\n\n
SUMMARY:📢 Mid-Evaluation Rubric (CS 492-C1\,C2\,C3\,C4\,C5\,C6)
UID:d7d8930d-04c7-4f54-a8c2-0b6410c3a14c@d7d8.org
