DESCRIPTION:Link: https://hulms.instructure.com/courses/5111/discussion_topics/62289\n\nDear all\,\nI am planning Quiz 1 on Monday. I have just uploaded combined slides for lectures 4-6 (i.e. Monday January 26th - Monday February 2nd). These include concepts which were covered as Python demos.\nAll the concepts you will be tested on are in the slides for Lectures 1 through 6.\nI will also upload slides for today's session (Lecture 7)\, although it will not be tested in the quiz. More precisely\, today's session was a review session\, however\, we did go over the LSTM\, and what extra abilities it has\, over regular RNNs.\nOf the topics we have covered previously\, backpropagation and regularization will not be tested in the quiz.\nBest\,Usama
